OL,6,FShe says she is aware of people
OL,7,Fexperiencing discrimination when
OL,8,Fapplying for jobs or a housing tenancy.
OL,10,FEvita describes: "I believe I heard
OL,11,Fmuch more years ago but I'm still
OL,12,Fhearing stories. In those two sectors,
OL,13,Fthere is still a lot of work that
OL,14,Fneeds to be done."
OL,16,FAnti-discrimination legislation was
OL,17,Fintroduced in Guernsey in October 2023
OL,18,F, offering more protection to people
OL,19,Fwho are discriminated against on the
OL,20,Fgrounds of characteristics such as
OL,21,Fdisability or race.
